#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:6
msgid "How to re-run failed tests and maintain state between test runs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:11
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:13
msgid ""
"The plugin provides two command line options to rerun failures from the last "
"``pytest`` invocation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:16
msgid ":option:`--lf, --last-failed <--lf>` - to only re-run the failures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:17
msgid ""
":option:`--ff, --failed-first <--ff>` - to run the failures first and then "
"the rest of the tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:20
msgid ""
"For cleanup (usually not needed), a :option:`--cache-clear` option allows to "
"remove all cross-session cache contents ahead of a test run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:23
msgid ""
"Other plugins may access the `config.cache`_ object to set/get **json "
"encodable** values between ``pytest`` invocations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:28
msgid ""
"This plugin is enabled by default, but can be disabled if needed: see :ref:"
"`cmdunregister` (the internal name for this plugin is ``cacheprovider``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:34
msgid "Rerunning only failures or failures first"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:36
msgid "First, let's create 50 test invocations of which only 2 fail:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:38
msgid ""
"# content of test_50.py\n"
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"i\", range(50))\n"
"def test_num(i):\n"
"    if i in (17, 25):\n"
"        pytest.fail(\"bad luck\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:49
msgid "If you run this for the first time you will see two failures:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:51
msgid ""
"$ pytest -q\n"
".................F.......F........................                   [100%]\n"
"================================= FAILURES "
"=================================\n"
"_______________________________ test_num[17] "
"_______________________________\n"
"\n"
"i = 17\n"
"\n"
"    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"i\", range(50))\n"
"    def test_num(i):\n"
"        if i in (17, 25):\n"
">           pytest.fail(\"bad luck\")\n"
"E           Failed: bad luck\n"
"\n"
"test_50.py:7: Failed\n"
"_______________________________ test_num[25] "
"_______________________________\n"
"\n"
"i = 25\n"
"\n"
"    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"i\", range(50))\n"
"    def test_num(i):\n"
"        if i in (17, 25):\n"
">           pytest.fail(\"bad luck\")\n"
"E           Failed: bad luck\n"
"\n"
"test_50.py:7: Failed\n"
"========================= short test summary info "
"==========================\n"
"FAILED test_50.py::test_num[17] - Failed: bad luck\n"
"FAILED test_50.py::test_num[25] - Failed: bad luck\n"
"2 failed, 48 passed in 0.12s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/cache.rst:83
msgid "If you then run it with :option:`--lf`:"
